The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 September is 72,206 (8,322.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 September, there were 1,893 new confirmed cases (218.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 September, there were 2,300 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 18% (407 fewer cases).
